The paper deals with unsupervised feature selection, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The regularized formulation proposed in the paper is relevant to the field of machine learning, specifically in the area of regularization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization algorithms, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of feature selection in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also relevant. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
